**Structure Reasoning:** Opens with the macro colour story to frame the season, then works through 9 key shades in order of search demand and editorial coverage. H10 provides the decision-making framework readers actually need. H11 covers the finish layer that every competitor skips — a real topical authority differentiator. H12 adds longevity/prep, which brings in nail health adjacent searches and signals expertise. Internal links distribute naturally across H5 (floral link), H3/H4 (almond link), and the intro/closing (pillar and polish links).

**Image Count Recommendation:** 14–18 images. One hero shot, one per major shade section (9 images), one or two for the skin tone / undertone section (hand comparison shots), one finish comparison flat lay, one nail prep closing image. This matches and slightly exceeds the top-ranking competitor range while being more intentional with image-to-section mapping.

