## VOICE AND TONE RECOMMENDATION

**Recommended Voice:** Confident colour editor — the friend who actually works in the industry and gives you a straight answer instead of listing every shade ever made.

**Tone Characteristics:**
- Direct and opinionated — willing to say "butter yellow is fading" and back it up with data
- Warm but authoritative — no hedging, no "it really depends on everyone"
- Specific — shade names, finish types, and skin tone guidance are concrete
- Data-grounded — cite Fresha search figures (+467% butter yellow, +2,100% polka dots, +450% jade marble), Pinterest Predicts 2026, and salon booking trends where they support a point
- British English throughout (colour, grey, favourite, jewellery)

**Language Style:** Use "you" directly throughout. Short, punchy paragraphs. No jargon without explanation. Avoid beauty press-release clichés. Every sentence should either teach something or help the reader make a decision.

**Audience Match:** This reader is trend-aware but time-poor. She wants to know what to book at her next appointment or what to click on the brand site — not an essay. Curated, confident, and action-oriented.

